      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are right that this pain feels permanent because the loss of identity is real, but your worth was never tied to that company or the money. The shame you feel is a reaction to the situation, not a reflection of your actual value as a human being. Even if the world sees you as a failure now, you still have your own thoughts, your own capacity to feel, and that is enough to begin rebuilding.",
